That's the old sergeant.

415
00:32:18,169 --> 00:32:21,605
Here are the commitment papers
for the Smith child.

416
00:32:21,673 --> 00:32:23,106
Yes, sir.

417
00:32:23,174 --> 00:32:26,541
If they'd been prepared weeks ago, you
could have saved considerable trouble.

418
00:32:26,611 --> 00:32:28,306
You're quite right, Mr. Carmichael.

419
00:32:28,379 --> 00:32:32,816
See that the child is taken to the
orphanage in the morning. That's all.

420
00:32:35,787 --> 00:32:37,721
Get me the orphanage.

421
00:32:45,663 --> 00:32:47,096
Come in.

422
00:32:50,702 --> 00:32:54,103
- Well, good morning.
- Good morning.

423
00:32:54,172 --> 00:32:57,437
- I thought you were going to Rome.
- Venice.

424
00:32:57,508 --> 00:33:00,170
Oh, yes, of course. Venice.

425
00:33:00,244 --> 00:33:03,372
Well, I've postponed that, but I've
been postponing it all my life...

426
00:33:03,448 --> 00:33:05,473
so once more won't hurt.

427
00:33:05,550 --> 00:33:07,677
We have a proposition
we want to make.

428
00:33:07,752 --> 00:33:09,344
Won't you be seated?

429
00:33:09,420 --> 00:33:10,853
You bet.

430
00:33:16,961 --> 00:33:20,988
There's no need to hide.
Move your chair out there.

431
00:33:21,065 --> 00:33:25,058
We have a problem, a situation that
confronts a lot of people these days.

432
00:33:25,136 --> 00:33:26,728
We want to be let alone.

433
00:33:26,804 --> 00:33:30,900
That's all we ask of the United States,
New Jersey, Union County and you.

434
00:33:30,975 --> 00:33:35,912
If you'll just tell us what you want of
us, we'll see what we can do about it.

435
00:33:35,980 --> 00:33:38,744
All I want is to see Patsy
properly provided for.

436
00:33:38,816 --> 00:33:40,681
What do you mean,
"properly provided for"?

437
00:33:40,752 --> 00:33:43,118
I mean properly
clothed and properly fed...

438
00:33:43,187 --> 00:33:45,485
in a home where her schooling
won't be neglected...

439
00:33:45,556 --> 00:33:47,888
where she won't be subjected
to the wrong sort of influence.

440
00:33:47,959 --> 00:33:49,620
Oh. Meaning me.

441
00:33:49,694 --> 00:33:52,993
- If the shoe fits.
- It pinches.

442
00:33:53,898 --> 00:33:56,298
Hey, where are you going?

443
00:33:56,367 --> 00:34:00,565
I won't live with anybody else but you
and Gramp! And they can't make me!

444
00:34:00,638 --> 00:34:03,937
Come on back and sit down,
or I'll walk out on the whole thing.

445
00:34:04,008 --> 00:34:06,340
As I understand it
your chief objection...

446
00:34:06,411 --> 00:34:10,609
is neither Gramp nor I is what you'd
call regularly or gainfully employed.

447
00:34:10,681 --> 00:34:12,205
- Correct.
- Well.

448
00:34:12,283 --> 00:34:16,652
If I can show you we're engaged in a
going business, would that be all right?

449
00:34:16,721 --> 00:34:17,949
What kind?

450
00:34:18,022 --> 00:34:21,856
We went into a little huddle
and decided to open a restaurant.

451
00:34:21,926 --> 00:34:23,917
We're gonna call it
"The Haunted House Cafe."

452
00:34:23,995 --> 00:34:26,657
- It was my own idea.
- Quiet, Patsy. Now, listen.

453
00:34:26,731 --> 00:34:30,189
The place where we happen to be living
has the reputation of being haunted.

454
