<i>Just as I hope you will</i>
<i>while I'm waitin'for you</i>

900
01:08:36,112 --> 01:08:39,138
- Hi. Now, here's the plan.
- What plan?

901
01:08:39,215 --> 01:08:42,878
- You're checking out of here.
- Larry! And I thought she was kiddin'.

902
01:08:42,952 --> 01:08:45,147
- Who was kidding?
- Susan Sprague.

903
01:08:45,221 --> 01:08:46,950
She promised
she'd get me out of here.

904
01:08:47,022 --> 01:08:50,014
Get you out of here? If it wasn't
for her, you wouldn't be here.

905
01:08:50,092 --> 01:08:53,584
That female Iscariot framed you
the moment I turned my back.

906
01:08:53,662 --> 01:08:57,291
That's what I thought. But she said
she didn't have anything to do with it.

907
01:08:57,366 --> 01:09:00,392
- She even lost her job because of us.
- How do you know?

908
01:09:00,469 --> 01:09:02,903
She was in to see me,
and she told me.

909
01:09:02,972 --> 01:09:06,373
- And she said that she... Oh. Oh.
- Well, what did she say?

910
01:09:06,442 --> 01:09:10,606
Well, she made me promise not to tell
a living soul, especially you.

911
01:09:10,679 --> 01:09:13,546
- Tell me! Tell me now!
- Oh, it's nothing important.

912
01:09:13,616 --> 01:09:15,743
It's a secret.
Do you want me to break my word?

913
01:09:15,818 --> 01:09:19,083
I'll break your neck
if you don't tell me. Come on.

914
01:09:19,155 --> 01:09:22,682
Well, she said she liked you...

915
01:09:23,626 --> 01:09:25,685
a lot, an awful lot.

916
01:09:25,761 --> 01:09:29,094
She says the first time she saw you,
she fell in love with you.

917
01:09:29,165 --> 01:09:31,633
And the more she saw you
the worse it got.

918
01:09:31,700 --> 01:09:33,930
- And she said that...
- Now listen.

919
01:09:34,003 --> 01:09:38,372
If you're lying to me, I'm gonna let you
stay in this place till you're 108!

920
01:09:38,440 --> 01:09:43,275
Oh, but I'm not lying, Larry.
I'd never tell a lie.

921
01:09:43,345 --> 01:09:45,370
Now look, here's
what we're gonna do.

922
01:09:56,225 --> 01:09:59,319
She ate too much spinach.

923
01:10:00,529 --> 01:10:02,121
Come here.

924
01:10:05,434 --> 01:10:07,800
Come on. Make it fast.
Come on!

925
01:10:45,641 --> 01:10:47,666
Five, six...

926
01:10:49,812 --> 01:10:51,905
seven, eight...

927
01:10:53,215 --> 01:10:55,149
nine, ten.

928
01:11:40,362 --> 01:11:42,796
That's the man.

929
01:11:44,566 --> 01:11:48,093
Susan Sprague's in New York, and
that's the place to find Larry Poole.

930
01:11:56,111 --> 01:11:57,578
Come in.

931
01:11:59,648 --> 01:12:01,240
- Miss Sprague?
- Yes.

932
01:12:01,317 --> 01:12:03,683
- We're from the police department.
- What can I do for you?

933
01:12:03,752 --> 01:12:07,119
Now don't be alarmed. We just came up
to get a little information.

934
01:12:07,189 --> 01:12:11,250
- What about?
- We're trying to find a Larry Poole.

935
01:12:11,327 --> 01:12:14,296
Well, what makes you think
that I know his whereabouts?

936
01:12:14,363 --> 01:12:18,060
The last thing he said before he left
was that he was gonna look for you.

937
01:12:18,133 --> 01:12:20,863
What do you want him for?
What are the charges against him?

938
01:12:20,936 --> 01:12:22,665
Who said there was a charge?

939
01:12:22,738 --> 01:12:25,536
We wanna have a few words
with the man, that's all.

940
01:12:25,607 --> 01:12:28,303
I suppose that anything
I say will be used against me.

941
01:12:28,377 --> 01:12:30,743
Not at all.
We got nothin' on you.

942
01:12:30,813 --> 01:12:32,872
It's Larry Poole we're after.

943
01:12:32,948 --> 01:12:35,610
All you've got to do
is tell us where he is.

944
01:12:35,684 --> 01:12:40,519
Well, to the best of my information
and belief, Mr. Poole is in...

945
01:12:40,589 --> 01:12:42,352
- Venice.
- Venice?

946
01:12:42,424 --> 01:12:44,483
That's in Italy.

947
01:12:50,065 --> 01:12:51,532
Come in.

948
01:12:56,305 --> 01:12:59,138
- Here's your laundry.
- Thanks.

949
01:13:00,142 --> 01:13:02,076
What's that?

950
01:13:02,144 --> 01:13:04,840
That's a map
of New York City.

951
01:13:09,718 --> 01:13:12,380
What are all those
little pins for?

952
01:13:13,389 --> 01:13:16,324
Oh, that's a long story.

953
01:13:16,392 --> 01:13:18,326
I've got plenty of time.

954
01:13:18,394 --> 01:13:22,797
Well, each one of those little pins
represents a backyard.

955
01:13:22,865 --> 01:13:27,234
I'm making sort of a tour
of all the backyards in New York City.

956
01:13:27,302 --> 01:13:30,897
- What for?
- I'm looking for somebody.

957
01:13:32,007 --> 01:13:33,975
- Are you a G-man?
- No.

958
01:13:34,042 --> 01:13:38,809
- Who are you looking for?
- A girl.

959
01:13:38,881 --> 01:13:43,181
- When you find her, what'll you do?
- Do you have to know?

960
01:13:45,554 --> 01:13:48,455
But I'd like to know.
You've got me all excited.

961
01:13:48,524 --> 01:13:51,493
Listen, if I tell you,
will you keep it to yourself?

962
01:13:51,560 --> 01:13:53,323
Oh, sure.

963
01:13:53,395 --> 01:13:55,829
If I find that girl,
I'm going to get down on my knees...

964
01:13:55,898 --> 01:13:57,991
and apologize to her
for being such a fool...

965
01:13:58,066 --> 01:14:00,159
as to misunderstand her
for even a moment.

966
01:14:00,235 --> 01:14:04,035
I'm going to ask her
to forgive me.

967
01:14:04,106 --> 01:14:08,008
If you'll excuse me, I've got
a lot of backyards to cover today.

968
01:14:15,584 --> 01:14:20,612
<i>The breeze runs after you</i>

969
01:14:20,689 --> 01:14:24,785
<i>When you're passing by</i>

970
01:14:24,860 --> 01:14:28,819
<i>It wants to be near</i>

971
01:14:28,897 --> 01:14:33,027
<i>And so do I

972
01:14:33,101 --> 01:14:37,435
<i>The willow bows to you</i>

973
01:14:37,506 --> 01:14:41,442
<i>Forgetting to cry</i>

974
01:14:41,510 --> 01:14:45,139
<i>It waits for your smile</i>

975
01:14:45,214 --> 01:14:49,412
<i>And so do I

976
01:14:49,485 --> 01:14:53,353
<i>All the world's at your command</i>

977
01:14:53,422 --> 01:14:56,323
<i>What wouldn't it do</i>

978
01:14:56,391 --> 01:15:00,054
<i>For one look at you</i>

979
01:15:00,128 --> 01:15:03,154
<i>And I'm</i>

980
01:15:03,232 --> 01:15:07,066
<i>That way too</i>

981
01:15:07,135 --> 01:15:13,040
<i>The rose that you caress</i>

982
01:15:13,108 --> 01:15:18,068
<i>Is willing to die</i>

983
01:15:18,146 --> 01:15:23,778
<i>It loves you so very much</i>

984
01:15:23,852 --> 01:15:29,381
<i>And so</i>

985
01:15:29,458 --> 01:15:33,895
<i>Do I

986
01:15:56,718 --> 01:15:58,709
Oh, am I glad I found you.

987
01:15:58,787 --> 01:16:01,347
- You know I was down to my last pin?
- What pin?

988
01:16:01,423 --> 01:16:03,755
Wait till I get my breath.

989
01:16:05,294 --> 01:16:08,855
Well, go ahead.
Slap my face. It was worth it.

990
01:16:08,931 --> 01:16:10,558
Oh, don't be silly.

991
01:16:10,632 --> 01:16:13,829
- I've been looking all over for you.
- You've been looking for me?

992
01:16:13,902 --> 01:16:15,597
Gee, I've been
looking for you for weeks.

993
01:16:15,671 --> 01:16:18,697
Why, I even put an ad
in the personal column.

994
01:16:18,774 --> 01:16:21,607
Larry, you shouldn't be here.
The police are looking for you.

995
01:16:21,677 --> 01:16:25,078
- You've got to leave town.
- Leave town is right.

996
01:16:27,649 --> 01:16:28,016
I'm not going to eat!
I'm on a hunger strike!

997
01:16:28,016 --> 01:16:30,450
I'm not going to eat!
I'm on a hunger strike!

998
01:16:30,519 --> 01:16:34,011
I've lost three pounds in the last
two days, and I'll be dead soon!

999
01:16:34,089 --> 01:16:36,853
She's perfectly capable
of carrying out her threats.

1000
01:16:36,925 --> 01:16:39,359
Mr. Carmichael, I've got
my own health to consider.

1001
01:16:39,428 --> 01:16:42,454
I'm on the verge
of a nervous breakdown.

1002
01:16:49,137 --> 01:16:50,729
So they found you, Poole.

1003
01:16:50,806 --> 01:16:54,435
Yeah, I decided to come on back
and take my medicine.

1004
01:16:54,509 --> 01:16:56,409
Patricia, come back here.

1005
01:16:56,478 --> 01:16:59,276
- No.
- See? That's what I get all the time.

1006
01:16:59,348 --> 01:17:01,873
Now, I want this matter
settled here and now.

1007
01:17:01,950 --> 01:17:04,544
You've got to take this demon
out of my institution.

1008
01:17:04,620 --> 01:17:08,249
She's disrupted the discipline,
tried to set fire to the place...

1009
01:17:08,323 --> 01:17:10,791
smashed the furniture,
broken the windows...

1010
01:17:10,859 --> 01:17:12,850
and now it's a hunger strike.

1011
01:17:12,928 --> 01:17:15,624
And if I don't die of hunger,
I'm gonna jump out of the window.

1012
01:17:15,697 --> 01:17:18,131
I've written a letter
blaming everything on you...

1013
01:17:18,200 --> 01:17:22,159
and I'm going to mail it to
all the newspapers before I kill myself!

1014
01:17:22,237 --> 01:17:25,934
You see! You've got
to do something about this...

1015
01:17:26,008 --> 01:17:28,442
even if you have to
adopt her yourself.

1016
01:17:28,510 --> 01:17:32,776
Me? I'd rather resign my job.
Young man...

1017
01:17:32,848 --> 01:17:35,544
you said you were ready
to take your medicine.

1018
01:17:35,617 --> 01:17:38,609
It may prove to be bitter medicine,
but you've got to help me out.

1019
01:17:38,687 --> 01:17:41,781
- Help you out?
- Yes, with this brat.

1020
01:17:41,857 --> 01:17:44,724
We've had nothing but trouble
ever since we sent her to the orphanage.

1021
01:17:44,793 --> 01:17:49,355
Shortly after she came there, carnival
people put on a show for the children.

1022
01:17:49,431 --> 01:17:52,366
She tore open the bass drum
and tried to escape in it.

1023
01:17:52,434 --> 01:17:55,733
Since then, she's made life
miserable for everybody.

1024
01:17:55,804 --> 01:17:59,331
She refuses to go
with anybody but you.

1025
01:17:59,408 --> 01:18:04,141
- Couldn't you take her off our hands?
- Well... Huh?

1026
01:18:04,212 --> 01:18:06,510
You mean to say that's why
you had those cops bring me here?

1027
01:18:06,581 --> 01:18:09,812
I'm terribly sorry, but you see
the desperate situation I'm in.

1028
01:18:09,885 --> 01:18:11,944
You're the only one
in the world who can help.

1029
01:18:12,020 --> 01:18:14,648
And there was no other way
of finding you.

1030
01:18:14,723 --> 01:18:17,487
Well, I guess you boys know
the penalties for false arrest.

1031
01:18:17,559 --> 01:18:19,424
Who said you were
under arrest?

1032
01:18:19,494 --> 01:18:22,486
We were told to find you
and bring you here, and we did it.

1033
01:18:22,564 --> 01:18:25,829
First, you do everything to put this
child in an orphanage, and I'm the goat.

1034
01:18:25,901 --> 01:18:27,869
Now you're doing everything
under the sun to have her...

1035
01:18:27,936 --> 01:18:30,029
taken out of the orphanage,
and I'm still the goat.

1036
01:18:30,105 --> 01:18:33,905
Looks to me like I'm "Joe Goat" around
here. Why should I do anything for you?

1037
01:18:33,975 --> 01:18:38,207
It isn't for me. I'm only acting
in the best interest of Patricia here...

1038
01:18:38,280 --> 01:18:40,771
this poor little motherless child.

1039
01:18:42,084 --> 01:18:44,143
Well, Susan,
what do you think?

1040
01:18:44,219 --> 01:18:46,949
First of all, I think
Mr. Carmichael owes you an apology.

1041
01:18:47,022 --> 01:18:50,219
I do, and I apologize
most humbly.

1042
01:18:50,292 --> 01:18:53,227
- And you owe Miss Sprague an apology.
- I do.

1043
01:18:53,295 --> 01:18:55,229
- Hey, what about me?
- Shut up!

1044
01:18:55,297 --> 01:18:58,858
And then I think Patsy should be adopted
by a respectable married couple.

1045
01:18:58,934 --> 01:19:02,802
Well, what's the matter with us?
Aren't we respectable?

1046
01:19:02,871 --> 01:19:07,638
Yeah, what's the matter with them?
Oh, let's eat. I'm just dying of hunger.

1047
01:19:07,709 --> 01:19:10,109
Say good-bye to the nice man.

1048
01:19:10,178 --> 01:19:12,305
G... Oh. No, never mind.

1049
01:19:49,017 --> 01:19:52,646
<i>When I'm waitin'for you</i>

1050
01:19:52,721 --> 01:19:55,349
<i>Three, four</i>
<i>Open up the door</i>

1051
01:19:55,423 --> 01:19:58,756
<i>Now hurry, dear</i>
<i>Hurry, for heaven's sake</i>

1052
01:19:58,827 --> 01:20:03,264
<i>I count each step you take</i>
<i>when I'm waiting for you</i>

1053
01:20:06,034 --> 01:20:10,471
<i>Five, six, now my heart does tricks</i>
<i>as I picture all your charms</i>

1054
01:20:10,539 --> 01:20:12,803
<i>Seven, eight</i>
<i>You're at the gate</i>

1055
01:20:12,874 --> 01:20:16,332
<i>And you make me dizzy</i>
<i>when you're walking right into my arms</i>

1056
01:20:16,411 --> 01:20:19,312
<i>Nine, ten, kiss me again</i>

1057
01:20:19,381 --> 01:20:22,009
<i>Tell me you get such a thrill</i>

1058
01:20:22,083 --> 01:20:24,449
<i>Just as I hope you will</i>

1059
01:20:24,519 --> 01:20:26,817
<i>When I'm waiting for you</i>

1060
01:20:28,356 --> 01:20:29,948
Hey, hey, hey!
Look out there!

1061
01:20:30,025 --> 01:20:33,722
Hey, hey!
Look out! Look out!

